    <parallel-safe>true</parallel-safe>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>Edit `projects/spaarke-daily-update-service/notes/playbooks/notification-work-assignments.json` (PB-022). Node graph: Start → `LookupUserMembership(sprk_matter)` → `QueryDataverse` (`sprk_workassignment` records linked to membership matters, created or updated within last 24h) → `CreateNotification`. Redeploy via MCP `update_record` on PB-022. Include Component Justification block.</prompt>

  <role>SPAARKE platform developer. Follow ADRs strictly. JPS playbook designer.</role>

  <goal>`notification-work-assignments.json` is a fully functional playbook (no longer a stub). Deployed PB-022 row reflects the full graph. `jps-validate` passes. AC-9 satisfied (when a sprk_workassignment linked to user's memberships is created or updated, an appnotification row appears).</goal>

  <context>
    <background>R4 spec FR-9 (line 148) replaces the PB-022 stub with a working implementation. Single-entity query (sprk_workassignment) filtered to membership-scope matters and 24h time window. Simpler than PB-017's 3-entity union but same canonical pattern. Component Justification: existing=stub PB-022, extension=Yes (functional promotion), cost-of-doing-nothing=users get zero work-assignment notifications.</background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>projects/spaarke-daily-update-service/notes/playbooks/notification-work-assignments.json</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-daily-update-service/notes/playbooks/notification-new-documents.json</file>
